man name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Robert Mildenhall was born in 1342, in Ramsbury, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom as the son of Thomas De Mildenhall. He had at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"1342–":"1342–Surnud","1330–Male":"1330–Surnud","1340–1391":"1340–1391","1342–Male":"1342–Surnud","1372–1440":"1372–1440","1300–Male":"1300–Surnud","1300":"1300","1342":"1342","1440":"1440","1330":"1330","1340":"1340","1372":"1372","1391":"1391","Ramsbury, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom":"Ramsbury, Wiltshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1342–":"1342–Kuollut","1330–Male":"1330–Kuollut","1340–1391":"1340–1391","1342–Male":"1342–Kuollut","1372–1440":"1372–1440","1300–Male":"1300–Kuollut","1300":"1300","1342":"1342","1440":"1440","1330":"1330","1340":"1340","1372":"1372","1391":"1391","Ramsbury, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom":"Ramsbury, Wiltshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1342–":"1342–Décédé","1330–Male":"1330–Décédé","1340–1391":"1340–1391","1342–Male":"1342–Décédé","1372–1440":"1372–1440","1300–Male":"1300–Décédé","1300":"1300","1342":"1342","1440":"1440","1330":"1330","1340":"1340","1372":"1372","1391":"1391","Ramsbury, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom":"Ramsbury, Wiltshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Robert Mildenhall est né en 1342, à Ramsbury, Wiltshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, fils de Thomas De Mildenhall. Il a eu au moins 1 fille."},"de":{"1342–":"1342–Verstorben","1330–Male":"1330–Verstorben","1340–1391":"1340–1391","1342–Male":"1342–Verst